edu.biu.scapi.interactiveMidProtocols.ot
Class OTOnGroupElementSMsg

java.lang.Object
  edu.biu.scapi.interactiveMidProtocols.ot.OTOnGroupElementSMsg
All Implemented Interfaces:
OTSMsg, java.io.Serializable
public class OTOnGroupElementSMsg
extends java.lang.Object
implements OTSMsg

Concrete implementation of OT Privacy sender (on GroupElement) message.

In the GroupElement scenario, the sender sends four GroupElements - w0, w1, c0 and c1.

This class is used by most of OT implementations.

An OT protocol that does not use this class (like OT SemiHonest) will create a separate class that matches what it needs.

Author:
Cryptography and Computer Security Research Group Department of Computer Science Bar-Ilan University (Moriya Farbstein)
